---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const heroImage = `${base}images/longtail-morning.jpeg`;
---

<Layout title="Tinvail | Our Story" description="The story behind Tinvail and the travel-inspired prints that shape the collection.">
  <section class="container-custom section-block">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.1fr] items-start">
      <div class="card-collection">
        <img src={heroImage} alt="Watercolor print of a woman walking along a calm beach" loading="lazy" width="900" height="1100" />
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="section-label">Our Story</p>
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl text-ink">Where the dreaming became true</h1>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-ink-soft max-w-xl">
          <p>
            Over the past seven years, I traveled through 67 countries. I stood barefoot on endless beaches. I found
            myself in forgotten temples, hidden deep in the jungle. Walked untamed paths, surrounded by silence and
            life at the same time, and watched sunsets that softened something inside me.
          </p>
          <p>With every place, I changed.</p>
          <p>
            The world did not just show me beauty, it showed me strength. It taught me how to listen to myself again.
            How to trust my intuition. How to love the woman I was becoming.
          </p>
          <p>
            In those quiet moments, I discovered something new, the power to create. Not for approval. Not for
            perfection. But from truth.
          </p>
          <p>
            I began to capture these memories and create something new from them. These experiences filled me. Each
            picture became proof that I could shape my own reality, that I could turn feeling into form, dreams into
            something real. They gave me energy, courage, and space to grow beyond fear and into self-love.
          </p>
          <p>Now, I want to share this with you.</p>
          <p>
            I want you to step into untouched nature with me. To feel the warmth, the stillness, the freedom. To
            travel to the most beautiful places on earth. Not to escape your life, but to return to yourself.
          </p>
          <p>
            Tinvail is a reflection of my journey. A reminder that healing, beauty, and creation begin the moment you
            allow yourself to believe again.
          </p>
          <p class="font-display text-xl text-ink">Because: "Dreaming starts with open eyes"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
